byline.contributor: Wai Moe contributed reporting from Yangon, Myanmar, and Saw Nang from Mandalay, Myanmar.

abstract: Myanmar’s new leader Daw Aung San Suu Kyi shuns spotlight while working on gradual transfer of power from military junta to first democratically elected government in over 50 years; emphasizes reconciliation and cooperation with old regime for benefit of country's future; some question competence and small size of her inner circle given enormity of challenges she faces.
lead_paragraph: Ms. Aung San Suu Kyi has kept the country guessing on details of the transfer of power to her democracy movement from the military establishment.

headline.main: After Victory in Myanmar, Aung San Suu Kyi Quietly Shapes a Transition
headline.print_headline: Behind the Scenes in Myanmar, a Transition Slowly Starts to Take Shape

snippet: Ms. Aung San Suu Kyi has kept the country guessing on details of the transfer of power to her democracy movement from the military establishment.
